Basic Git Workflow
Working Directory
       ↓
git add
       ↓
Staging Area
       ↓
git commit
       ↓
Local Repository
       ↓
git push
       ↓
GitHub / Remote Repo


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


📁 1. Initialize Git : 


FIrst Create Git repo in current folder : 

git init

📌 Use this command when:

Starting Git tracking for a project.

📌 Example:

You downloaded or created a project and want Git enabled.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

👤 2. Configure Git : 

This is command to Set username New Mechine or ennvironment : 

git config --global user.name "Madhan"

Next step Set email : 

git config --global user.email "yourmail@gmail.com"

Check config : 

git config --list

📌 Use when:
First-time setup.

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🔍 3. Check Status : 

git status

📌it Shows:

Modified files
Untracked files
Staged files

📌 Use constantly.

This is one of the MOST used commands.

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


➕ 4. Add Files to Staging : 

if want to Add one file use this command : 

git add index.js


if want to Add all files current directory use this one :

git add .


📌 Use when:

You want Git to prepare files for commit.

_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


💾 5. Commit Changes : 

git commit -m "Added login feature"

📌 Use when:

You completed a logical change or feature.

🧠 Think of commit as:

📸 A snapshot of your project.

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


📜 6. View Commit History : 

git log

Short version : 

git log --oneline

📌 Use when:

use this command if You want to see previous commits/history.

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🔗 7. Connect GitHub Repository : 

Use this command to Add remote Repo in Local Before using push in first time : 

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git


Then verify the Repo you're going to push by using this command : 

git remote -v


📌 Use when:

Connecting local project to GitHub.



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🚀 8. Push Code to GitHub : 

First push : 

git push -u origin main

Normal push later :

git push 

📌 Use when:

Uploading commits to GitHub.



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


📥 9. Pull Latest Changes : 

git pull 

Better version 

git pull origin main --rebase

📌 Use when:

Before starting work OR before pushing to repo.


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


📦 10. Clone Existing Repository : 

git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git 

📌 Use when:

Downloading project from GitHub.



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



🌿 11. Branch Commands : 

Create branch :

git branch feature-login


use this command for Switch branch :

git checkout feature-login


This is simple and combined command for Create + switch together :

git checkout -b feature-login


This command is for Show branches : 

git branch



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🔀 12. Merge Branch : 

git merge feature-login

📌 Use when:

Combining feature branch into main branch.


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

❌ 13. Remove Changes : 

Discard file changes : 

git checkout -- file.txt

Remove staged file : 

git reset file.txt


Reset everything ::

git reset --hard

( ⚠️ Dangerous — removes changes permanently.)


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



⏪ 14. Undo Commits

Undo last commit but keep changes : 

git reset --soft HEAD~1

Completely remove last commit : 

git reset --hard HEAD~1



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🔄 15. Rebase

git pull origin main --rebase

OR

git rebase main

📌 Use when:

Keeping clean commit history.


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🧹 16. Stash Changes : 

Save temporary work : 

git stash

if you want to Restore it use this command :

git stash pop

📌 Use when:

Need to switch branches without committing unfinished work.


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🏷️ 17. Tags :::

Create tag : 

git tag v1.0


Push tags :

git push --tags


📌 Use when:

Creating releases.



______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🔐 18. SSH Setup (Better than HTTPS) :::

Generate SSH key for Github Push : 

ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "yourmail@gmail.com"

Start SSH agent : 

eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"


Add key : 

ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

📌 Use when:

Avoiding PAT/password every push.

( still there's permission command and test command needs to include this list )

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



📊 19. See Differences :::

Show unstaged changes : 

git diff

Show staged changes : 

git diff --staged


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🔥 20. Force Push :::

git push --force

⚠️ But this is Dangerous Because it will Overwrites remote history (( mostly don't use this command in office environment )).... 


